---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Policy"
  description="How Electrician Times selects, writes, reviews and updates its articles, and how we handle corrections, guest posts and safety guidance."
  canonical="/editorial-policy/"
>
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ name: 'Home', href: '/' }, { name: 'Editorial Policy' }]} />
  <div class="container page-body">
    <h1>Editorial Policy</h1>
    <p>
      Electrician Times publishes practical articles about electrical work, tools, devices and
      safety. This page explains how our content is produced and maintained.
    </p>

    <h2>Accuracy and sources</h2>
    <p>
      We aim to describe electrical concepts, products and practices accurately. Where articles
      discuss standards or regulations, readers should always confirm the requirements that apply
      in their own country and jurisdiction, since electrical codes differ significantly between
      regions and change over time.
    </p>

    <h2>Safety-first approach</h2>
    <p>
      Electricity can injure or kill. Our articles are informational and are not a substitute for
      professional training. We consistently recommend that installations, repairs and any work on
      live circuits be carried out by licensed, qualified electricians in accordance with local
      regulations.
    </p>

    <h2>Guest contributions</h2>
    <p>
      We accept guest articles that fit our topics — see <a href="/write-for-us/">Write for Us</a>.
      Guest posts are reviewed before publication, and we reserve the right to edit for clarity,
      formatting and safety. Links within guest posts do not constitute endorsements.
    </p>

    <h2>Corrections and updates</h2>
    <p>
      If you spot an error, please <a href="/contact-us/">contact us</a>. We review reported issues
      and update or correct articles as needed. Updated articles show a “last updated” date.
    </p>

    <h2>Advertising and affiliate content</h2>
    <p>
      Where content is sponsored or contains affiliate links, we aim to keep editorial judgement
      independent of commercial relationships.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
